  "texts": [
    "For instance, pattern recognition algorithms have been shown to facilitate microfossil categorization based on distinct morphological traits, enhancing the efficiency of image analysis (Carvalho et al. 2020; Bollmann et al. 2004).",
    "Alternative strategies in work published to date, employ foundational ML models to infer classifications from historical data, providing more consistent outcomes than manual techniques (Peters et al. 2014).",
    "Despite these advancements, semi-automatic methods struggle to cope with the growing scale and intricacy of microfossil datasets (Carvalho et al. 2020), underscoring the need for more sophisticated DL-based methods with the potential to revolutionize microfossil analysis.",
    "Criteria Description/note Year Publication year Study title Title of the paper ML/DL technique Method: ML or DL Data information Task addressed (classification, or segmentation) Class and image counts Source of data Dataset name, if mentioned Image modality (e.g., 3D, 2D, SEM, Thin section) Preprocessing Preprocessing: Yes/No Techniques, if mentioned Augmentation Augmentation: Yes/No Techniques, if mentioned Network model DL model type (e.g., CNN) Model evaluation Metrics (e.g., Accuracy) Visualization (e.g., Loss curves) Results Performance (e.g., 98% Accuracy) Data/code availability Dataset link (optional) Model code link (optional) DL models, particularly CNNs (Ansari et al. 2023), have demonstrated remarkable efficacy in image-based tasks pertinent to microfossil image analysis, surpassing the constraints of traditional and semi-automatic techniques.",
    "This transformative shift in fossil image analysis methodologies is illustrated in Fig. 3."
  ]
}